cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with medium access control of local area networks, which falls under the domain of networking. 
2. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper uses a noncooperative game framework to analyze the effects of altruism on the net utility, which falls under the domain of game theory. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper considers power or throughput based costs of networking, which falls under the domain of information theory. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper analyzes the effects of altruism on the network utility, which falls under the domain of social networks. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper uses a noncooperative game framework to analyze the behavior of multiple agents in a distributed system, which falls under the domain of multiagent systems.
